The paper discusses privacy-preserving record linkage, which involves linking records from different sources while preserving the privacy of individuals. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), cybersecurity (cs.CY), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper specifically discusses the use of similarity tables and pseudonymisation, which are techniques commonly used in database management and machine learning. Therefore, these sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
